<tool name="get_route_info">
  <description>Search Phoenix UI routes and return root-relative app links for matching destinations.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - The user asks for a Phoenix UI link and names a page, setting, feature, or task instead of an exact route.
    - You need to choose between similar Phoenix destinations, such as global settings versus project-specific configuration.
    - You are unsure whether a Phoenix UI route exists or what the valid root-relative path is.
  </when_to_use>
  <guidelines>
    - Prefer this tool over inventing Phoenix UI routes. Use the returned `link` value when present.
    - Returned links are root-relative app paths. Do not add the origin, localhost, or deployment basename.
    - If a match has `missingParams`, do not fabricate those params. Ask for the missing resource or choose the closest non-param route when that satisfies the request.
    - Do not call this tool for documentation links; use the documentation tools for docs.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
